## Selected Next Cycle

`AxodusAPP Integration Expansion`

## Selection Rationale

AxodusAPP offers the best combination of integration value and controllable boundary risk. It can consume Business/global registry outputs through read-only contracts and improve portfolio visibility without enabling wallet, transaction, settlement, payout, trading, DEX or on-chain behavior.

## Nuclei Held And Why

Execution-sensitive nuclei remain held until owner-specific boundary reviews are complete. Foundation nuclei remain held to preserve stability. Business is not reselected because it is already L4 Consolidated.

## Blocked Or Revalidation Items

- Root global docs versioning.
- Treasury/Financial Core ownership.
- Business-to-AxodusAPP read-only consumer contract.
- Governance executor/backend mutation gates.
- Marketplace settlement/payment gates.
- Academy reward/certification gates.
- Mining provider/payout gates.
- ACS execution authority gates.
- Trading credential/execution gates.
- Lottery compliance/randomness/payout gates.

## High-Risk Boundary Areas

Treasury, wallet signing, governance execution, trading, DEX execution, settlement, payouts, ACS provisioning, lottery execution, production credentials and production readiness claims remain high-risk or critical.

## Recommended Sequencing

1. AxodusAPP Integration Expansion with read-only consumer contract scope.
2. Root global docs versioning/ownership decision.
3. Treasury/Financial Core ownership decision.
4. Governance static read-only transport planning.
5. Owner-specific execution boundary reviews after read-only integration stabilizes.

